RESILIENCE

Your Response

But now, back to you!

 

When facing stress, there are four main ways we react:

(Check out how one can lead to the others)

Your Thoughts

Your Body

Your Emotions

Your Behaviour

Your Thoughts

What you think (or 'your cognitive response')

 

You may become indecisive,  become very black and white in your approach, assume the worst or take things personally

Your Body

The physical response within your body. Your breathing and heart rate get faster, you sweat, your tummy can do backflips - and your mouth gets dry (basically, you can feel rotten!)

Your Emotions

The emotional reactions that then take over. You might go on a downer, get angry or anxious - or burst into tears more easily than usual.

Your Behaviour

What behavioural response then takes over. You start disengaging from others, snapping or arguing with people. Sleep might suffer, you get klutzy and start injuring yourself doing the simplest things, you might stay in bed longer – drug and alcohol use may even increase.
